x4freetext: Absolute emission probability per one fission (BIN+TER)
Cf-251 sample was prepared in Institute of Nuclear
Chemistry of Mainz University, Germany.
Sample activity 10.8 MBq, weight 5 microg.
Isotopic composition (06/06/07):
Cf-252 - 0.11% . As Cf oxide deposited on Ti-foil.
Deposit  diameters 4 mm. Sample was placed in center of
vacuum chamber at angle 45 deg with respect to incident
neutron beam. Sample was covered by polyamide foil.
PF1B cold neutron guide at ILL  -
for neutron induced fission.
Two deltaE-E telescopes, each
consisting of deltaE and E silicon surface barrier
detectors well-calibrated. Placed on both sides of
sample perpendicular to incident beam.
DeltaE detectors were covered by 30 microm Al foils.
DeltaE detector thickness - 1500 microm,
E detector thickness - 55.1/62.9 microm.

x4freetext: Absolute emission probability per one fission (BIN+TER)
Neutron flux at sample position about 3.5E+9 n/s/cm**2.
PF1B cold neutron guide at ILL  -
for neutron induced fission.
Cf-249 sample, deposited on a Ti foil, almost 100%
pure, 5.84 microg mass. Sample was placed in center of
vacuum chamber at angle 45 deg with respect to
incident neutron beam. Sample activity 0.9 MBq.
Prepared in LBNL, USA.
As Cf oxide deposited on Ti-foil.
Deposit  diameters 6 mm .
Sample was covered by polyamide foil.
Two deltaE-E telescopes, each
consisting of thin deltaE and thick E silicon surface
barrier detectors. Placed on both sides of sample at
about 4 cm distance and perpendicular to beam.
DeltaE detectors were covered by 30 microm Al foils.
DeltaE detector thickness - 1500 microm,
E detector thickness - 49.8 microm.
Measurement was performed in 3 steps:
1.Sample was placed to face the deltaE-E telescope.
Al foil was removed. DeltaE detector was replaced by
an empty dummy. Binary fission events were detected.
2. Measurement of ternary alpha-particles using
deltaE-E telescope. 30 microm Al foil was put in front
of telescope to stop fission fragments and Cf-249 decay
alphas. 29.8 microm deltaE and 500 microm E telescope
allows good separation between LRA particles and
background.
3. Sample was turned over 90deg angle to place in
front of DeltaE-E telescope. 30 microm Al foil covered
telescope. 49.8 microm deltaE and 1500 microm E
telescope  was used to measure the ternary triton and
alpha yields simultaneously.
FWHM of triton energy distribution with average
energy KE at ternary fission.
Table 3 of C,2007CORSEN - average KE and it`s
FWHM; Table 4 - abs. emission probability.
Table 1 of C,2007NICE,1,479,2007
Data of C,2007NICE were replaced by data
of C,2007CORSEN as newer publication.
PRT/FIS -> PRD/FIS according to comment N.Otsuka,NDS.
